AHCWRK311 Undertake Site Inspections  

This template allows you to record your observations, findings, and recommendations during a site inspection. 

 

Worksheet Template: Site Inspection 

 

Date: _____________ 

Site: ______________ 

 

Inspector: ______________ 

 

Objective: The objective of this worksheet is to guide students in conducting a site inspection and documenting their observations, findings, and recommendations. 

 

Instructions: 

1. As you conduct the site inspection, fill in the checklist below by marking the appropriate checkboxes or providing the requested information. 

2. Take notes, record any concerns or findings, and capture photographs if necessary. 

3. Use the space provided at the end to summarize your observations, findings, and recommendations. 

 

General Site Conditions: 

- Verify site location and boundaries. 

- Assess accessibility and entry points to the site. 

- Evaluate site conditions, including topography, soil type, vegetation, and drainage. 

- Identify any existing infrastructure or features that may impact the inspection. 

 

☐ Verified site location and boundaries. 

☐ Assessed accessibility and entry points. 

☐ Evaluated site conditions (topography, soil type, vegetation, drainage). 

☐ Identified existing infrastructure or features impacting the inspection. 

 

Environmental Considerations: 

- Assess the presence of protected flora or fauna species. 

- Evaluate potential impacts on the environment (erosion, habitat destruction, contamination risks). 

- Determine compliance with relevant environmental legislation and regulations. 

- Note any areas of conservation significance or special ecological value. 

 

☐ Assessed presence of protected flora or fauna species. 

☐ Evaluated potential impacts on the environment. 

☐ Verified compliance with environmental legislation and regulations. 

☐ Noted areas of conservation significance or ecological value. 

 

Work Practices and Procedures: 

- Observe and evaluate work practices and procedures on-site. 

- Assess compliance with occupational health and safety regulations. 

- Identify potential risks and hazards. 

- Review implementation of control measures to mitigate risks. 

 

☐ Observed and evaluated work practices and procedures. 

☐ Assessed compliance with health and safety regulations. 

☐ Identified potential risks and hazards. 

☐ Reviewed implementation of control measures. 

 

Equipment and Machinery: 

- Inspect equipment and machinery used on-site. 

- Ensure equipment is in safe working condition. 

- Check for proper maintenance and service records. 

- Verify compliance with relevant industry standards. 

 

☐ Inspected equipment and machinery. 

☐ Ensured equipment is in safe working condition. 

☐ Checked maintenance and service records. 

☐ Verified compliance with industry standards. 

 

